HEADWORD: Hypertrophy
<hw>Hy*per"tro*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"ype`r</grk> over, beyond + <?/ nourishment, fr. <?/ to nourish:
cf. F. <ets>hypertrophie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med. & Biol.)</fld> <def>A
condition of overgrowth or excessive development of an organ or part; --
the opposite of <ant>atrophy</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
